data.text: cheerful ♦ bright ♦ cheery ♦ jolly ♦ merry ♦ in a good mood

data.chText: 以上各词均形容人快乐的心情和这种心情的表露。
data.enText: All these words describe people who feel happy and show this in their behaviour.

data.chText: 指快乐的、高兴的、兴高采烈的：
data.enText: happy and showing it in your behaviour or expression

data.chText: 快快乐乐、勤奋工作的雇员
指人或神色快活而生气勃勃：
data.enText: (of a person or their expression) cheerful and lively

data.chText: 他感到兴高采烈，浑身充满活力。
data.enText: He felt bright and cheerful and full of energy.

data.chText: 用cheerful还是bright？
形容人时，bright用于bright and cheerful短语中或动词be/feel之后：
data.enText: When describing people, bright is used in the phrase bright and cheerful or after the verbs be/feel .

data.chText: 我那天早上心情不是很欢快。
data.enText: I was not feeling very bright that morning.

data.chText: 表示快乐的男孩 / 女孩可用cheerful boy/girl；bright boy/girl指男孩 / 女孩聪明，而不是指欢快。
data.enText: You can say a cheerful boy/girl but a bright boy/girl is intelligent, not cheerful.

data.chText: 指人或举止欢快起劲：
data.enText: ( informal ) (of a person or their manner) cheerful

data.chText: 那一端的接线员欢快而轻松。
data.enText: The telephonist at the other end was cheery and casual.

data.chText: 指人或举止高兴的、兴高采烈的：
data.enText: ( rather informal ) (of a person or their manner) cheerful

data.chText: 经理胖乎乎乐呵呵的。
data.enText: The manager was fat and jolly.

data.chText: 指人或举止欢乐：
data.enText: ( literary ) (of a person or their manner) cheerful

data.chText: 一群兴高采烈的村民观看了仪式。
data.enText: A merry crowd of villagers watched the proceedings.

data.chText: 用cheery、jolly还是merry？
以上各词均形容人的举止、外表或行为而非他们的内心感受。jolly和merry听起来稍显过时。jolly通常用于体型肥大的人，cheery可用于任何体型的人。
data.enText: All these words describe sb's manner, appearance or behaviour more than their inner feelings. Jolly and merry can sound slightly old-fashioned. Jolly people are often large and fat; cheery people can be any shape or size.

data.chText: 指人心情、情绪好：
data.enText: (of a person) feeling happy so that you behave well to other people, usually because sth good has happened to you

data.chText: 他那天心情不好。
data.enText: He was not in a good mood that day.

value.def: Someone who is jolly is happy and cheerful in their appearance or behaviour.

example.ex: She was a jolly, kindhearted woman.
example.tran: 她是个心地善良、整天乐呵呵的女人。

value.tran: 兴高采烈的；快乐的；高兴的

value.def: A jolly event is lively and enjoyable.

example.ex: I was looking forward to a jolly party...
example.tran: 我期待着有一个令人愉快的聚会。

example.ex: She had a very jolly time in Korea.

value.tran: 令人愉快的；欢快的；惬意的

value.def: Jolly is sometimes used to emphasize an adjective or adverb.

example.ex: She was jolly good at jigsaws...
It was jolly hard work, but I loved it.
example.tran: 这可是件很苦的差事，不过我喜欢。

value.def: Jolly well is sometimes used to emphasize an opinion or intention, and to express annoyance or anger.

example.ex: We can hardly just tell him what we jolly well think of him can we?...
example.tran: 我们不能就这么直接地告诉他我们到底是怎么看他的，是吧？

example.ex: She was jolly well not going to let them get away with it.
example.tran: 她肯定不会在这件事上就这么放过他们。

value.tran: （用于强调看法或意图，表示恼火或生气）当然，无疑，真是
